question:

subject: Mo BETTA
value: You are very patient and fair even in when things become complex or we hit a wall. I  appreciate your desire to deeply understand all the complexities of code and to follow the highest standards. It shows your commitment to becoming a viable engineer in the industry and your commitment to contributing to the success of the learners to come. I think it would benefit you to trust in the "process of cognitive apprenticeship and that some things are learned layer by layer as opposed to seeing a concept for a week and understanding how the whole thing works by the end of the week. That's very difficult for anyone to do -  to let go of what has worked for me in the past and trust that with the pro learners, cognitive apprenticeship, your own efforts in gathering information and practice over a long period of time will pull the pieces together. I also think we all need to bring up the feelings about the new group coming in and define our roles in their learning and talk about "not knowing" how to do things that they may need help with to get done. We aren't their teachers. I really appreciate your work style and look forward to  working with you again.

"{{subject}}, I want to work with you because... and I would want to work with you more if..."
subject: John Roberts
value:
Jrob, I want to work with you because I have a strong appreciation for how you approach software architecture. It's been very interesting to see how Floworky as a project has adapted to the realities of having so many newbie devs working on it, and you have so much to teach me with regards to the specific (mostly soft) skills that I need to learn.

I'd want to work with you more if you didn't seem so overwhelmed with your time commitments. I felt like the entire onus for communication was on me, and even when I tried to communicate, you weren't particularly available. That is not something that works well with my disability, which I feel like I've had next to no support with handling in this context.

I'd also want to work with you more if I felt more encouraged and supported to genuinely push myself on a technical level. I have a huge pre-existing tension/trigger around not being 'allowed' to be as effective as I can be, and I am EXHAUSTED to the point of being at a genuine personal breaking point from having such a difficult time getting up to technical ZPD and out of soft-skills panic zone.
